Program: The History Hour
Title: The Aboriginal Tent Embassy
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p04q9rdl
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 29 Jan 2017
On 26 January 1972 four Aboriginal men began a protest outside Parliament House in Canberra, Australia. They erected a beach umbrella on the grass and called it an 'embassy'. Plus, the murder of five lawyers in Madrid in 1977, which became a turning point in Spain's return to democracy; the invention of the microwave oven; Roald Dahl's Charlie and the Chocolate Factory; and 75 years of the BBC's longest-running programme, Desert Island Discs. Show less